###############################################################################
# NOTES & TIPS
###############################################################################

# REST Client Extension Tips:
# 1. Use @baseUrl variable defined at top of file
# 2. Comments start with # or //
# 3. Use ### to separate test requests
# 4. Click the "Send Request" link above each request
# 5. Response appears in "Response" tab on the right
# 6. Use Ctrl+Alt+L to format JSON
# 7. Use Ctrl+Shift+D to duplicate request
# 8. Environment variables can be defined with @ prefix

# Expected Response Codes:
# 200 - OK (successful GET, DELETE)
# 201 - Created (successful POST)
# 400 - Bad Request (validation errors)
# 404 - Not Found (resource doesn't exist)
# 409 - Conflict (duplicate room name)
# 429 - Too Many Requests (rate limit exceeded)
# 500 - Internal Server Error (unexpected error)

# Testing Workflow:
# 1. Start fresh database: rm data/neighborhood.db && python src/main.py
# 2. Run this test file from top to bottom
# 3. Monitor terminal output for logs
# 4. Check response status and body
# 5. Verify data in database: PRAGMA table_info(table_name);
